com.nerjal.json.elements

Class JsonArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nerjal.json.elements.JsonElement
      • com.nerjal.json.elements.JsonArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<JsonElement>

    public class JsonArray
extends JsonElement
implements Iterable<JsonElement>

    An object that lists JSON values, allowing to build arrays for a JSON structure.

    The object provides list of values, accessible with their indexes in the array, and iterable using most common methods. Eg.

    
  JsonArray.forEach(UnaryConsumer<JsonElement>)
 
 
  for (JsonElement : JsonArray) {}
 
  while (JsonArray.iterator.hasnext() {
      JsonArray.next();
  }

    Warning! Iteration with indexes includes all JsonComment in the list. Thus retaining indexes while iterating with the included iterator might cause errors.

    The objects stringification relies on options set with a ArrayParseOptions attribute, defaulted to match the JSON4 syntax, which can be replaced or instantiated to a different value.
    These options allow to set how many elements are put on each line, from one to putting all in one line. (exception being for single-line comments, which are still followed by a line break)

    Author:
    nerjal

      • stringify

        public String stringify(String indentation,
                        String indentIncrement,
                        com.nerjal.json.elements.JsonStringifyStack stack)
                 throws JsonError.RecursiveJsonElementException
        Description copied from class: JsonElement
        Returns the JSON String corresponding to this JsonElement, recursively parsing the internal elements if there are, with the according base indentation and level indent incrementation.
        Parameters:
        indentation - the base indentation at which should be the element, hence the one-lower level of its children
        indentIncrement - the string to increment to the indentation at each indentation level, recursively to the element's children as well as their own, etc.
        stack - The foolproof security check to avoid recursive stringification. Can be null.
        Returns:
        The JSON String corresponding to this element.
        Throws:
        JsonError.RecursiveJsonElementException - If the element or one of its children contains an element already in the stack or one of themselves, which would end up in loop parsing.

      • forAll

        public void forAll(Consumer<JsonElement> action)
        Performs the given action for each element of this list until all element have been processed or the action throws an exception.
        This includes JsonComment elements.
        Actions are performed in the order of iteration. Exceptions thrown are relayed to the caller.
        This method won't allow editing this list but only its elements during iteration.
        Parameters:
        action - the action to be performed for each element
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified action is null
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the action tries to append, remove, or replace elements in this list
